        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Corner Peel &#38; Stanley Streets<lb/>
            South Brisbane<lb/>
            Queensland Jan 13&#47;77<lb/></p>
            <p>The Revd. S. <sic>Morris</sic><lb/>
            My dear Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Your kind favor of the 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. Octr.<lb/> reached me today &#38; I hasten to reply thereto.<lb/></p>
            <p>I now perceive the great omission<lb/> in my last with respect to the description of<lb/> the party sought after &#38; altho&#39; I now send you<lb/> the same&#44; I must admit to vagueness&#44; &#38; trust<lb/> at the same time it may in some way aid you in the search.<lb/></p>
            <p>Be pleased to understand that<lb/> the present description may not of its own accuracy<lb/> identify Mr Goldman&#44; as he no doubt may have<lb/> much altered in the course of eleven or Twelve<lb/> years&#44; but at the time he was last seen&#44; he was<lb/> according to the statement of my requisitionist<lb/> &#40;who is a foreigner&#41; about 45 years of age&#8212;of<lb/> middle stature&#44; dark complexion&#44; with an<lb/> inclination to be stout&#8212;this is all I can give<lb/> you.<lb/></p>
            <p>It appears likely to me&#44; if a person<lb/> of the above description be met&#8212;he might be asked<lb/> if he were at any time in Queensland&#8212;if found<lb/> that he had been in Queensland his identity would<lb/> then be established&#44; for he was then &#38; up till now<lb/> the only person of that name in the Colony<lb/></p>
            <p>It is also possible should he have<lb/> died the Board of Health may have a record<lb/> of the place whence he came&#8212;viz Queensland<lb/> but the greatest probability appears to be that<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>if dead he was buried by &#91;Hebrew&#93; &#38; they<lb/> would surely record the fact in the<del>ir</del> <lb/> books of the Synagogue<lb/></p>
            <p>It is difficult for me to conjecture<lb/> how the &#91;Hebrew&#93; are situated in your city<lb/> but in these Colonies&#8212;there is not a single<lb/> Jewish individual who is not known &#38;<lb/> recognized by some one&#8212;it is no matter<lb/> where he might happen to come from&#8212;should<lb/> it &#91;&#63;&#93; be from India &#38; China Figis or<lb/> elsewhere&#45;&#45;&#38; judging from ourselves I am<lb/> led to believe that a private inquiry<lb/> among individuals especially &#40;foreign &#91;Hebrew&#93;&#41;<lb/> would effect the purpose&#45;&#45;&#38; I am the more<lb/> inclined to think so&#44; from your statement&#45;&#45;<lb/> &#34;for many persons of the name of Goldman<lb/> have lived &#38; died in our city&#34;&#45;&#45;if it were<lb/> possible to discover if one came from or<lb/> had been in Queensland&#8212;the matter would<lb/> be then settled.<lb/></p>
            <p>I thank you for the h&#91;&#63;&#93; teaching<lb/> the law&#8212;as it would affect the marriage<lb/> of the parties in question&#8212;but I find<lb/> that the parties married &#40;not before a<lb/> magistrate&#41; but a Registrar&#8212;which is<lb/> about the same thing on the strength of<lb/> the information received that Mr. G. was<lb/> dead&#45;&#45;&#38; that prior to this marriage my<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>requisitionist gave Mrs. G. protection<lb/> &#38; shelter only from alleged cruelty of her husband<lb/> Then if the information they had gotten was<lb/> a fact&#44; I would submit that the <sic>impedimt</sic><lb/> is removed &#38; the law<lb/> will not apply to them &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have nothing further to add<lb/> but to commit the care of this matter<lb/> to your hand with the hope that<lb/> your kind endeavours will lead to<lb/> a successful issue<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain<lb/>
            My Dear Sir<lb/>
            Yours faithfully<lb/>
            A. P. Phillips<lb/></p>
            
            <p>In order to facilitate this matter<lb/> &#38; to bring it to a close&#8212;Would you<lb/> kindly in your reply enclose a<lb/> memo of any cost &#38; expenses<lb/> this affair may have put you to<lb/></p>
            <p>APP<lb/></p>
            <p>Please address as above<lb/></p>
        </body>
